Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `arr` must have a length between 1 and 200.
- All values in the integer array parameter `arr` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 1000000.
- The integer parameter `k` must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to the length of the integer array parameter `arr` minus 1.
- The integer result is the minimum total space wasted if the array can be resized at most `k` times.